api/issue/619647.actaulResult: Below are cases I tried:   1  {code}s-venta-inmuebles/cuauhtemoc-df/departamento/v1c1097l10270a1dwp1?pr=12347,13000&ba=10&be=1&priceType=FIXED {code}  - works    bapi call: {code}GET /v1/ads?creationDateZoomOutDays=1&url=/s-venta-inmuebles/cuauhtemoc-df/departamento/v1c1097l10270a1dwp1?pr%3D12347,13000&ba=10&be=1&priceType=FIXED{code}   2  {code}s-venta-inmuebles/cuauhtemoc-df/departamento/v1c1097l10270a1dwp1?be=1&pr=12347,13000&ba=10&priceType=FIXED {code} - doesn't work, only defference is queries's order  bapi call: {code}GET /v1/ads?creationDateZoomOutDays=1&url=/s-venta-inmuebles/cuauhtemoc-df/departamento/v1c1097l10270a1dwp1?be%3D1&pr=12347,13000&ba=10&priceType=FIXED{code}   3 {code}s-venta-inmuebles/cuauhtemoc-df/departamento/v1c1097l10270a1dwp1?be=1&pr=12347,13000 {code}  - doesn't work although without price type,   {code}s-venta-inmuebles/cuauhtemoc-df/departamento/v1c1097l10270a1dwp1?priceType=FIXED{code} - works  so I think it not related with pricetype but query orders    4 {code}s-venta-inmuebles/cuauhtemoc-df/departamento/v1c1097l10270a1dwp1?be=6&pr=12347,13000&ba=44{code} - be work but pr/ba don't work  {code}s-venta-inmuebles/cuauhtemoc-df/departamento/v1c1097l10270a1dwp1?ba=44&pr=12347,13000&be=1{code} - ba works, but pr/be don't work    so the conclusion is that: all query parameters after pr don't work in searchSeoUrl if pr is not the first query parameter

The root cause I found is that the refund prepare batch job only picker the latest payment id for corresponding order.  For below ad, we can see there’re 2 payment records for order_id : 108098219  (106625662 and 106625663), the paid one is 106625662. Not the latest one.  If wants to fix the issue, we need to refactor the batch job and check through all orders and features under that ad.     suggest workaround: we can compare the ad feature start date whether today and end date exists there > now()
